article.headline: Norfolk State 55, N. Carolina A&T 43
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Karandick Ogunride scored 12 of his 13 points in the second half and grabbed 13 rebounds Saturday, leading Norfolk State past North Carolina A&T 55-43. The Spartans (6-12, 5-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) led 20-19 at halftime and opened the second half on a 15-5 run to lead 35-24 with 12:24 left. North Carolina A&T (3-14, 3-5) never got closer than nine again. Tynell Dunkley added 11 points and Tony Murphy 10 for Norfolk State, which limited the Aggies to 13 field goals and just 25.5 percent shooting. The Aggies got 12 points each from Trahern Chaplin and Jason Wills.
